lockers_and_study_spaces.title: As an admin I'm assigned to a library and don't need to select a library after logging in

comments.body:
Any new Locker Applications that admins create should be in their "home" library, they should not need to select a library. 

When the Lewis Patron feature is on:
  * Students will have a two step Locker Application Process, where they need to do the second step to mark application complete
  * Admins will have a one step Locker Application Process, where any application they create will be marked as complete

lockers_and_study_spaces.title: When I create a locker application it does not submit it.

comments.body: ~I think this *may* be fixed by https://github.com/pulibrary/lockers_and_study_spaces/pull/147~ (edit: not the case)

~I think this is actually a feature - the idea is that half-made applications don't clutter up the administrator's list. We may want to change it, but it was requested.~ (edit: clarified in comment below)

See duplicate bug #157 for more details.

While addressing this, we should make sure not to add any regressions on https://github.com/pulibrary/lockers_and_study_spaces/pull/142 -- particularly when the Lewis Patrons feature flipper is on.

When the Lewis Patron feature is off: 
  * Any new Locker applications should show in the Locker Applications List (should be marked "complete" - add `complete=true` as parameter if the feature flag is off)

When the Lewis Patron feature is on:
  * Incomplete Locker applications should not show in the Locker Applications List (those with only UID & Library)
  * Locker applications that are updated should be marked as complete and show on the Locker Applications List
